dct_title_s: Map of the City of Newark, State of New Jersey 1899
dct_description_sm: Map depicts recognized and unrecognized streets in the City of Newark in 1899. At the westernmost point is south nineteenth street, in the north is the Greenwood Lake division of the Erie RR, in the east is the passaic River & the southernmost point is Bound Creek.
